  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Draw samples from a Wald, or inverse Gaussian, distribution."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "As the scale approaches infinity, the distribution becomes more like a\nGaussian. Some references claim that the Wald is an inverse Gaussian\nwith mean equal to 1, but this is by no means universal."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The inverse Gaussian distribution was first studied in relationship to\nBrownian motion. In 1956 M.C.K. Tweedie used the name inverse Gaussian\nbecause there is an inverse relationship between the time to cover a\nunit distance and distance covered in unit time."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Extended Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Distribution mean, must be > 0."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "float or array_like of floats",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Distribution mean, must be > 0."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "mean",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Scale parameter, must be > 0."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "float or array_like of floats",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Scale parameter, must be > 0."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "scale",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "(m, n, k)"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": ", then\n"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "m * n * k"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " samples are drawn.  If size is "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "None"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " (default),\na single value is returned if "
                      },
                      {
                        "external_url": "",
                        "href": "/docs/api/numpy/mean/",
                        "kind": "link",
                        "target": "mean",
                        "text": "mean"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " and "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "scale"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " are both scalars.\nOtherwise, "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "flops.broadcast(mean, scale).size"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " samples are drawn."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "int or tuple of ints, optional",
